{"lemma":"أَطْعِمَةُ","slug":"أَطْعِمَةُ","root":"ط.ع.م","root_slug":"ط-ع-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ع-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَعام","root":"طعم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26728"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"food","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ بَل لَّبِثْتَ مِائَةَ عَامٍ فَٱنْظُرْ إِلَى طَعَامِكَ وَشَرَابِكَ لَمْ يَتَسَنَّهْ","english":"He said, “Rather, you have remained one hundred years. Look at your food and your drink; it has not changed with time.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"food; prepared meal","tags":["countable","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feeding","tags":["noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَحَاضُّونَ عَلَى طَعَامِ ٱلْمِسْكِينِ","english":"And ye urge not on feeding the poor."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wheat","tags":["al-Andalus","countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"وقيل إن نضح بقدر جرة من ماء الزيتون قدر مائة جرة من الطعام لم يفسد ولم تصبه آفة وإن نضح عليه ماء الأفسنتين بقي ولم يفسد.","english":"It is said that when a jar of wheat is dampened with a jar of amurca it does not suffer decay nor damage, and if it is dampened with absinthe water, it stays and does not rot."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grain, cereal","tags":["countable","uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew טַעַם (ṭāʿām)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.ʕaːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26728","headword_ar":"اطعمهُ","root":"TEm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEmhu AlT~aEaAma","text_ar":"اطعمهُ الطَّعَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iToEaAmN","text_ar":"اـِطْعَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave him to eat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave him food;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) [and so, accord. to modern usage, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TE~mhu","text_ar":"طعّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEmhu","text_ar":"اطعمهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He supplied him with the means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, in the Kur [li. 57],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA A^uriydu","text_ar":"وَمَا اُرِيدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yaToEimuwni","text_ar":"اَنْ يَطْعِمُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I desire not that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning] any of my servants"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"should supply me with the means of subsistence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for I am the supplier of the means of subsistence. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEamotuka h`*ihi AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"اَطْعَمْتُكَ هٰذِهِ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have assigned to thee as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomap","text_ar":"طُعْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEamahumo TuEomapF","text_ar":"اَطْعَمَهُمْ طُعْمَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assigned to them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave them, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEmp","text_ar":"طعمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Aboo- Haneefeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iToEaAmu","text_ar":"الاـِطْعَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies peculiarly (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lending of land for cultivation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is said on the authority of Mo'áwiyeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu A^aToEama EamorFA xaraAja","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ اَطْعَمَ عَمْرًا خَرَاجَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSora","text_ar":"مِصْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he gave 'Amr as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomap","text_ar":"طُعْمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrAj","text_ar":"خراج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land-tax"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Egypt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b4-  See also 10. ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEm AlguSona","text_ar":"اطعم الغُصْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iToEaAmN","text_ar":"اـِطْعَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ingrafted upon the branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoot, a branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoot, of another tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TE~mhu","text_ar":"طعّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is more commonly used in this sense,] (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taToEiymN","text_ar":"تَطْعِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TE~mhu","text_ar":"طعّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is now used as meaning also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inoculated him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEamotu Eayonahu","text_ar":"اَطْعَمْتُ عَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa*FY","text_ar":"قَذًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I cast a mote into his eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1854},{"kind":"text","text":"[―         -b7-  See also a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobapN","text_ar":"عِقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEm","text_ar":"اطعم"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~axolu","text_ar":"النَّخْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-trees had ripe fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as might be eaten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bore fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEmt Al$~ajarapu","text_ar":"اطعمت الشَّجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tree had ripe fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATEmt Alv~ayarapu","text_ar":"اطعمت الثَّيَرَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fruit became ripe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","ISh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}